ABAKALIKI- Operatives of the Nigeria Drugs Law Enforcement Agency(NDLEA), Ebonyi State Command, have sealed Grace Court Hotel and Suite, owned by former Governor of the State and Senator Representing Ebonyi North Senatorial District, Dr. Sam Egwu. The Hotel located at Nna street in Abakaliki, Ebonyi State capital, was sealed Monday morning over allegation that the hotel was a safe haven for illicit drug peddlers and consumers. The anti-drug agency, it was gathered, had on Sunday night, arrested some suspects allegedly in possession of large quantity of illicit drugs in the hotel. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! The operation was led by one Ibrahim Bashiru, who introduced himself to Journalists at the gate of the hotel, as the Deputy Commandant in charge of Operations and Intelligence of the Agency. Bashiru, however, refused to speak further on the matter, as according to him, he was not permitted to speak to Journalists. Anambra 2021: Okonkwo Picks PDP Governorship Nomination Form Kogi Rep Urges Gov Wike To Join 2023 Presidential Race Under PDP He said the Command would brief Journalists on the matter in due time, adding that anybody seen within the premises of the hotel would be arrested. One of the Operatives was seen carrying many mobile phones, indicating that some persons might have been arrested within the hotel premises and their phones confiscated by anti-drug Agency while sealing the hotel,Monday morning.